{
  "monologue": "I can't share my private chain-of-thought, but here's a concise rationale: given your BED challenges and your need for structure, using a single immediate micro-action after labeling the trigger helps interrupt cue-driven snacking, builds automaticity through repetition, and keeps you on a steady path toward your next milestone without overwhelming you.",
  "utterance": "After your planned snack, take 60 seconds to label the trigger, then perform one fresh micro-action you can do immediately (for example: a 60-second box-breathing exercise), and log it within 5 minutes. Keep a cue card by your snack area and note in your log how this supports BED management and your consistency goal. Small, consistent steps like this move you toward the next milestone.",
  "endkey": false
}
